==English==
===Noun===
'''joint''' (''plural'' '''joints''')

#(''anatomy'') Any part of the body where two [[bone]]s meet, in some cases allowing that part of the body to be bent or [[straighten]]ed.
#In any physical structure, the point where two components are connected, in such a way that the components can each rotate about that point.
#In any physical structure, the point where two components are fixed rigidly together and cannot move.
#:''The water is leaking out of the joint between the two pipes.''
#(''carpentry'') A means of joining two pieces of wood together so that they [[interlock]].
#(''slang'') A [[cannabis]] [[cigarette]].

====Synonyms====

*(''point where two components are connected, in such a way that the components can each rotate about that point''): [[hinge]]
*(''cannabis cigarette''): [[doobie]], [[reefer]], [[spliff]]

